**Scope:** This specification defines the triage logic for analyzing incoming text messages, computing a lethality score based on risk indicators (intent, means, immediacy), and routing conversations. It integrates with existing chat triage infrastructure, leveraging NLP models for sentiment analysis and evidence-based response generation. No changes to client-approved policies are implied.

## 1. Overview
The triage logic processes incoming text messages in real-time to detect high-risk mental health crises. It uses natural language processing (NLP) to extract indicators of suicidal or self-harm risk, assigns a lethality score (0-100), and applies routing rules:
- **High-risk (score ≥ 75)**: Route to human supervisor queue with priority escalation.
- **Medium-risk (score 50-74)**: Monitor with AI responses, including grounding exercises; escalate if score increases.
- **Low-risk (score < 50)**: Handle via AI with evidence-based grounding exercises and de-escalation prompts.

The system integrates with the existing BeaconCare chat platform, using Azure Cognitive Services for NLP and a custom scoring engine. All decisions are auditable, with logs stored in compliance with HIPAA and grant data retention requirements.

